info.title: Smoke

data.text: Ideal place for a lazy Sunday brunch. The build your own brekkie is to be recommended letting you choose your favourites. The black pudding is the tastiest ever and if you enjoy smoked food then the sausages and bacon will titillate your taste buds. My only gripe is they don’t supply Heinz baked beans ( just my traditional choice !) but have a 3 bean offer in it’s place. Grab yourself a complimentary newspaper lying around and chill whilst drinking your tea or coffee- what better way to spend a lazy Sunday morning.
data.name: Roger Watterson

data.text:
I love this place! I think it's my favorite place in Wilmslow.
The food is good and it is a fun and enjoyable establishment. The staff are mostly very nice and friendly and always make me smile. There were a few occasions where one or another employee wouldn't be as friendly and maybe seemed annoyed if you asked for something, but overall I would 100% recommend it.

data.text:
Visited today evening on account of my birthday with my family.
This cafe is right on the main road with many restaurants on both sides. A cute dinosaur prototype is kept on the terrace in the veranda outside. Must be ideal to visit in summer and sit outside enjoying the fresh air. Very centrally located.

Waiters were polite and gave an excellent and fast service. Wine was wonderful and the appetizers and side dishes were also good . Found the cheese to be very salty though. Red peppers were amazing. Would advise to increase vegetarian options in the menu. There are a few but would prefer more options considering the growing number of people turning vegetarian and vegan day by day. Also better for the environment and avoids animal cruelty.
Overall a great experience and would definitely visit again.
Regards
Dr Pratik from India.
data.name: Dr Pratik

data.text: Doesn’t cater for nut allergies. Doesn’t say it on the menu or Facebook site (website doesn’t work) & you can’t get the menus online, so we were in for brunch & settled with drinks, then found out when ordering food. Didn’t offer a single option. We all understand the caution, but it’s almost 2022 - being able to prep something in a clean area or cut fruit away from other food is hardly an unrealistic standard. The food my friends ate looked lovely, but service was also severely lacking - sat upstairs & there was no one to order a second drink from for over 20mins despite 5 x serving & bar staff downstairs and it wasn’t overly busy - same situation with the bill, gave up and went downstairs in the end, finding all 5 servers behind the bar.

data.text:
We were going to Camarena next door and noticed that Smoke is now open (need to publicise this!) so we popped in for a couple of drinks.
The decor is great, with the black interior giving a stylish and intimate feel. The barman was really friendly and helpful and there was a good atmosphere.
A great selection of beers on tap with the the bar staff knowing their stuff and able to describe each one and allowing a taster. We will definitely be back for food next time.
